+# Changelog
+
+All notable changes to this project are documented in this file.
+
+The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
+and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html)
+with pre-1.0 (`0.x`) conventions: breaking changes increment the **minor**, and
+backward-compatible work increments the **patch**.
+
+## [0.2.0] - 2026-05-27
+
+First tagged release. Establishes the version baseline at the Next.js platform
+migration; prior `0.1.x` development was untagged.
+
+### Changed
+
+- **BREAKING (platform):** Upgraded the runtime/build stack — `next` 14 → 16,
+  `react` / `react-dom` 18 → 19, `tailwindcss` 3 → 4, `typescript` 5 → 6,
+  `eslint` 9 → 10, and `@google/generative-ai` 0.21 → 0.24
+  (`73b4573`, `package.json`).
+- Migrated PostCSS to the Tailwind v4 plugin: `tailwindcss` + `autoprefixer`
+  plugins replaced by `@tailwindcss/postcss` (`postcss.config.mjs`).
+- Updated `tsconfig.json` and `globals.css` for the Next 16 / Tailwind 4 toolchain.
+
+### Removed
+
+- Dropped a redundant `useEffect` selection-sync in the demand-letter draft panel,
+  relying on derived state instead (`src/features/demand-letter/components/DraftPanel.tsx`).
+
+### Notes
+
+- This release captures the accumulated pre-1.0 feature set (demand-letter drafting,
+  discovery + RFA, settlement valuation, medical-records upload, citation gate) under
+  its first version tag.
+- A concurrent security scan flagged open items against this tree (no-auth dev tenant
+  seam, full-document CourtListener egress, postcss `<8.5.10` transitive XSS). These are
+  tracked separately and are **not** resolved by this release.
+
+[0.2.0]: https://github.com/xkazm04/ai-paralegal/releases/tag/v0.2.0
