+++ b/docs/adr/ADR-0001-credential-access-audit-log.md
+# ADR-0001 · In-app audit log for credential access events
+
+- **Status:** Proposed (awaiting stakeholder decision on requirement conflict — see Consequences)
+- **Date:** 2026-05-26
+- **Driver:** Idea `team.idea.accepted` — "Add a lightweight in-app audit log for credential access events"
+- **Author:** Solution Architect (automated review)
+
+## Context
+
+The idea ships with a stated requirement: *"Must fit the existing local-first SQLite +
+event-bus architecture; no cloud egress."* This requirement does **not** match the
+codebase that exists. Evidence from inspection:
+
+- **No SQLite, no event-bus anywhere.** `grep` for `sqlite`/`event-bus`/`EventEmitter`/`pubsub`
+  across `src/` and `docs/` returns nothing. Feature stores are ephemeral in-memory `Map`s
+  (`src/features/discovery/store.ts:13`, same pattern in matters/medical-records/settlement).
+- **The real event surface is structured logging.** `LogEvent` is a closed discriminated
+  union (`src/lib/logging/types.ts`) — today `ai_call`, `cite_verify`, `artifact_draft`,
+  `artifact_sign`, `record_upload`. `logEvent()` (`src/lib/logging/log.ts:7`) is the *only*
+  logger; bare `console.log` is an ESLint error. CULTURE.md §6 mandates: *"Adding a new event
+  type means extending the union first."*
+- **Production is cloud, not local-first.** README + CULTURE.md target Google Cloud Run with
+  Firestore, CMEK Cloud Storage, BigQuery, and Cloud Logging (stdout pipe in `logEvent`,
+  `log.ts:13`). The "30-day citation audit" already works by grouping `cite_verify` events in
+  Cloud Logging. So the existing audit substrate *is* cloud egress by design.
+- **Credentials are read in exactly one place today.** `process.env.GEMINI_API_KEY` in
+  `src/lib/ai/callAI.ts:88`. Future integration secrets (Clio, DocuSign, Twilio, Stripe — per
+  README) will add access points.
+- **Tenant identity is already on every event.** `TenantContext` (branded `tenantId`/`userId`/
+  `attorneyId`, `src/lib/tenant.ts`) is threaded through every call site, so credential-access
+  events get attribution for free.
+
+There is also a directly related backlog item — *"bar-grievance audit log immutable record"*
+(`docs/backlog-brainstorm.json:23`, effort 6 / impact 9). Credential-access auditing should be
+designed as a sibling of that append-only ledger, not a one-off.
+
+## Decision
+
+**Adopt the existing structured-event-log pattern. Add a `CredentialAccessEvent` variant to the
+closed `LogEvent` union and emit it via `logEvent()` at every credential-touch site. Do NOT
+introduce SQLite or an event-bus — neither exists, and adding them is net-new infrastructure
+that contradicts the Firestore/Cloud-Logging direction.**
+
+The "in-app audit log" view is a **read model over the existing logging sink** (Cloud Logging /
+BigQuery in prod; stdout/JSON in dev), surfaced through the established audit-drawer UX
+(`CitationAuditDrawer.tsx`, CULTURE.md "audit drawers behind numerical claims").
+
+**The "local-first SQLite + no cloud egress" clause is rejected as written** because it
+describes a different system. Two reconciliation paths are offered for stakeholder choice
+(see Consequences) — this ADR does not silently override the requirement, it surfaces the
+mismatch.
+
+## Consequences
+
+**Positive**
+- Zero new infrastructure; reuses the exhaustive-union + `logEvent()` pattern the team already
+  enforces. Credential events inherit tenant attribution and the SOC 2 / audit pipeline.
+- Type-safe: a missing variant in any consumer is a compile error.
+
+**Negative / risks**
+- **Requirement conflict (UNRESOLVED — needs human decision).** "No cloud egress" is
+  incompatible with the current audit substrate (Cloud Logging/BigQuery). This must be resolved
+  before Task 4 ships:
+  - **Path A (recommended):** treat "no cloud egress" as not applicable — credential-access
+    events flow to the same Cloud Logging sink as all other audit events. Consistent, lowest
+    cost. Risk: contradicts the literal idea text.
+  - **Path B:** honor no-egress by adding a durable *local* append-only sink (the current
+    in-memory Maps are ephemeral and unfit for an audit trail). This is genuinely net-new
+    persistence and partially contradicts the Firestore direction; scope it only if no-egress is
+    a hard compliance constraint for a specific tenant tier.
+- **Secret-leak hazard.** A credential-access event must log *that* a secret was accessed, never
+  the secret value. Schema must exclude the value; enforce in review/tests.
+- Coverage limitation: only `callAI.ts` reads a secret today, so initial instrumentation is thin
+  until the Clio/DocuSign/Twilio/Stripe integrations land.
+
+## Task breakdown (total: 14 points; 5 contingent on requirement decision)
+
+1. **(1 pt)** Add `CredentialAccessEvent` variant to `LogEvent` in `src/lib/logging/types.ts`
+   (fields: `credentialName`, `action: "read"|"use"`, `outcome: "ok"|"missing"|"error"`,
+   `tenantId`, `userId`, `purpose`). Value field explicitly excluded.
+2. **(2 pts)** Define the credential taxonomy + redaction rule (which env secrets are auditable;
+   "access" vs "use" semantics). Document in CULTURE.md §6 event-type list.
+3. **(3 pts)** Instrument access sites: emit at `callAI.ts:88` (GEMINI_API_KEY read, incl. the
+   `missing_api_key` branch) and add the helper for future integration secret reads.
+4. **(5 pts, BLOCKED on Path A/B decision)** In-app audit read model + viewer: query the logging
+   sink filtered to `credential_access`, render via an audit-drawer surface. Path B adds a
+   durable local sink instead.
+5. **(2 pts)** Tests: assert events are emitted on read/missing/error, assert the secret value
+   never appears in the payload (`callAI`-style test alongside existing `store.test.ts`).
+6. **(1 pt)** Update CULTURE.md §6 + this ADR status to Accepted once Path A/B is chosen.
+
+## Assumptions
+- None marked UNVERIFIED — all claims cite inspected files. Future integration secret locations
+  (Clio/DocuSign/etc.) are not yet in the repo; Task 3's helper anticipates them.
+

